  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AI agents remain impractical without standardized, scalable integrations to external business systems, positioning the Model Context Protocol (MCP) as the essential solution. Using the Mastra framework as a practical implementation guide, it demonstrates how MCP replaces fragile, service-specific API wrappers with a universal communication layer that simplifies tool discovery, per-user authentication, and composite workflows. The piece maintains a pragmatic, tutorial-adjacent tone while leveraging a USB-to-USB-C metaphor to frame MCP as an industry-standard connector that decouples agent logic from backend infrastructure. It is primarily aimed at AI developers and software engineers building production-ready, multi-tenant agentic applications in TypeScript.",
